text: Yttrium oxide is Y2O3. It is an air-stable, white solid substance. Yttrium oxide is used as a common starting material for both materials science as well as inorganic compounds. ==References== ==Other websites== * Yttrium oxide information at Webelements. * External MSDS Data Sheet .
